import torch


class Target(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()

    def preprocess(self, value):
        return torch.tensor(float(value))

    def forward(self, x):
        return x


class PersonDetector(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.linear = torch.nn.Linear(1024, 1)

    def preprocess(self, value):
        return torch.tensor(value).type(torch.float)

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.linear(x)[:, 0]

    def postprocess(self, x):
        return x.item() > 0.5


docs.create_model(
    'target',
    Target(),
    serializer='dill',
)

docs.create_model(
    'person_detector',
    PersonDetector(),
    serializer='dill',
)

    'person_detector',

    objective='bce',
    metrics=['accuracy'],
